album.title: King Of The Delta Blues Singers

wiki.content: Of the 29 tracks Johnson recorded in the 30's this is one of the more relished by blues and rock fans alike. This song has been covered by Eric Clapton, Robert Jr. Lockwood ( Robert Jonhson's stepson), The Allman Brothers Band, Lonnie Pitchford and many more. It was also sampled by Gare du Nord for their song Pablo's Blues User-contributed text is available under the Creative Commons By-SA License and may also be available under the GNU FDL.

track.name: Come On In My Kitchen
comments: Have all his recordings, like him.
You Gotta Move by The Rolling Stones sounds similar to this song..
The one who started it all! Enough said.
great tune...,also steve miller did a rockin` cover   that kicked ass !!!

So many rock bands covered Robert Johnson's songs.
Rolling Stones, Cream, Led Zeppelin, Black Crowes, Allman Brothers Band (just to name a few). Allman's did a great version of this song "Come On Into My Kitchen" really well .
Some say he made a deal with the devil at the crossroads, what do you think?
